                            <comment id="14202849" author="dimaspivak" created="Fri, 7 Nov 2014 22:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Out of the box, Jenkins doesn&apos;t treat flakey tests in a special way, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Flaky+Test+Handler+Plugin&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;there is a plugin&lt;/a&gt; that can change this. Perhaps worth checking with our friends at b.o.a. to get this set up, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
